kpi_info.title: period_duration (period_duration)
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_LCS_REQUESTS (M1011C0)
kpi_info.use: The number of received location requests from the CN to request information on the location of a given UE. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_RECEIVED_EM_LOCREQ (M1011C1)
kpi_info.use: The number of received location requests related to emergency calls. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_FAILED_LOCREQ (M1011C2)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed location requests. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_FAILED_EM_LOCREQ (M1011C3)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed location requests related to emergency calls. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FF_CID (M1011C4)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests, where accuracy codes are fulfilled by only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_REQ_FF_CID (M1011C5)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests, where accuracy codes are fulfilled by only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_NOT_FF_CID (M1011C6)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests, where either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled by only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_NOT_FF_CID (M1011C7)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests, where either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_HOR_NOT_FF_CID (M1011C8)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests, where horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_HOR_NOT_FF_CID (M1011C9)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests, where horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only cell ID/RTT method. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FAIL_CID (M1011C10)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed cell ID/RTT calculations for high priority location requests. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_FAIL_CID (M1011C11)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed cell ID/RTT calculations for normal or unknown priority location requests. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_FAILED_LOCREQ_DUE_ANC (M1011C12)
kpi_info.use: The number of location requests, which can not be served due to anchoring. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_REJ_LOCREQ_DUE_DUP (M1011C13)
kpi_info.use: Number of location requests, which are rejected, because a location request for the same UE is already in calculation. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: NBR_OF_CORE_REJ_SAI_REQUEST (M1011C14)
kpi_info.use: The number of Location Reporting Control messages received from CN requesting to stop reporting at the change of Service Area. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FF_AGPS (M1011C15)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests where accuracy codes are fulfilled by only A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and accuracy codes are fulfilled by only A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_REQ_FF_AGPS (M1011C16)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests where accuracy codes are fulfilled by only A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and accuracy codes are fulfilled by only A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_NOT_FF_AGPS (M1011C17)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests where either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled by A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled by A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_NOT_FF_AGPS (M1011C18)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests where either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is successfully calculated and either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_HOR_NOT_FF_AGPS (M1011C19)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated high priority location requests where horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is successfully calculated and horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_HO_NOT_FF_AGPS (M1011C20)
kpi_info.use: The number of successfully calculated normal or unknown priority location requests where horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is successfully calculated and horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using A-GPS method.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FAIL_AGPS (M1011C21)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed A-GPS calculations for high priority location requests. UPDATED:When A-GPS calculation fails for the location request in question.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_FAIL_AGPS (M1011C22)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed A-GPS calculations for normal or unknown priority location requests. UPDATED:When A-GPS calculation fails for the location request in question.

kpi_info.title: RRC_MEA_REP_W_AGPS_DATA_REQ (M1011C23)
kpi_info.use: The number of received RRC:Measurement Report messages with IE 'UE positioning GPS additional Assistance Data Request'. UPDATED:When RRC:Measurement Report message with IE 'UE positioning GPS additional Assistance Data Request' is received from UE.

kpi_info.title: LOC_RELATED_DATA_REQ (M1011C24)
kpi_info.use: The number of received Location Related Data Requests from CN. UPDATED:When RANAP: LOCATION RELATED DATA REQUEST message is received from CN with Requested Location Related Data Type IE value 'Dedicated Assistance Data for Assisted GPS' or 'Dedicated Assistance Data for UE Based OTDOA'.

kpi_info.title: ASSISTANCE_DATA_DELIV_AGPS (M1011C25)
kpi_info.use: The number of sent Assistance Data Delivery messages for Network Assisted GPS. UPDATED:When a RRC:Assistance Data Delivery message is sent for AGPS.

kpi_info.title: RRC_STATUS_ASS_DATA_DELIV (M1011C26)
kpi_info.use: The number received RRC Status messages with IE 'assistance data delivery'. UPDATED: When a RRC: STATUS message with IE 'assistance data delivery' is received from the UE.

kpi_info.title: LOC_REL_DATA_FAIL_NO_DATA (M1011C27)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed location related data requests due to dedicated assistance data is not available. UPDATED:When a RANAP:LOCATION RELATED DATA FAILURE message with cause "Dedicated Assistance Data Not Available" is sent to the CN.

kpi_info.title: AGPS_DATA_VOLUME_TO_UE (M1011C28)
kpi_info.use: The number of A-GPS assistance data bytes transmitted between RNC and UE. UPDATED:When RRC: ASSISTANCE DATA DELIVERY message is sent to UE.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C29)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for high priority location requests when accuracy codes are fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and accuracy codes are fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C30)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for normal priority location requests when accuracy codes are fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and accuracy codes are fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_NOT_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C31)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for high priority location requests when either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: OT_PRI_REQ_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C32)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for normal priority location requests when either horizontal or vertical accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and accuracy codes are fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_HO_NOT_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C33)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for high priority location requests when horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: OT_PRI_REQ_HO_NOT_FF_NW_AGPS (M1011C34)
kpi_info.use: The number of successful calculations for normal or unknown priority location requests when horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using only the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the location request in question is calculated and horizontal accuracy code is NOT fulfilled using the NW based A-GPS.

kpi_info.title: H_PRI_REQ_FAIL_NW_AGPS (M1011C35)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed calculations for high priority location requests when using the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the NW based A-GPS calculation fails for the location request in question.

kpi_info.title: OTHER_PRI_REQ_FAIL_NW_AGPS (M1011C36)
kpi_info.use: The number of failed calculations for normal or unknown priority location requests when using the NW based A-GPS method. UPDATED:When the NW based A-GPS calculation fails for the location request in question.

kpi_info.title: SUM_CIRTT_LATENCY (M1011C37)
kpi_info.use: The sum of CI+RTT method latency. Measured from the point when location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C38, gives the average CI+RTT method latency. This counter includes both normal requests and emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method, this counter is updated by the duration of the CI+RTT method.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_CIRTT_METHOD (M1011C38)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1011C37. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counter M1011C37 after a successful location calculation.

kpi_info.title: CIRTT_LATENCY_LESS_THAN_2_S (M1011C39)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage where the latency was less than 2 seconds. Measured from the point when location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. This counter includes both normal requests and emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was less than 2 seconds.

kpi_info.title: CIRTT_LATENCY_BETW_2_TO_5_S (M1011C40)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage where the latency was between 2 and 5 seconds. Measured from the point when location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. This counter includes both normal requests and emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was between 2 and 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: CIRTT_LATENCY_OVER_5_SEC (M1011C41)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage where the latency was over 5 seconds. Measured from the point when location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. This counter includes both normal requests and emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was over 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: SUM_GPS_LATENCY (M1011C42)
kpi_info.use: The sum of GPS method latency. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C43, gives the average GPS latency. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by UE based AGPS, NW based AGPS or standalone method, this counter is updated by the duration of the GPS method.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_GPS_METHOD (M1011C43)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1011C42. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counter M1011C42 after a successful location calculation.

kpi_info.title: GPS_LATENCY_LESS_THAN_5_S (M1011C44)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was less than 5 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by UE based AGPS, NW based AGPS or standalone method and the duration was less than 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: GPS_LATENCY_BETW_5_TO_15_S (M1011C45)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was between 5 and 15 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by UE based AGPS, NW based AGPS or standalone method and the duration was between 5 and 15 seconds.

kpi_info.title: GPS_LATENCY_OVER_15_SEC (M1011C46)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was over 15 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated by UE based AGPS, NW based AGPS or standalone method and the duration was over 15 seconds.

kpi_info.title: SUM_LCS_TOTAL_LATENCY (M1011C47)
kpi_info.use: The sum of total LCS latency, including RTT and RxTx measuring, CI+RTT method calculation and possible GPS positioning. Measured from the point when location request has been received by RRC to point when location response has been sent to CN from RRC. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C49, gives the average LCS latency. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated and the response has been sent to CN, this counter is updated by the duration of the location procedure.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_LCS_TOTAL_LATENCY (M1011C48)
kpi_info.use: The sum of squared LCS latency. Needed for standard deviation calculation. UPDATED:When the location of UE has been successfully calculated and the response has been sent to CN, this counter is updated by the squared duration of the location procedure.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_LCS_TOTAL_LATENCY (M1011C49)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counters M1011C47 and M1011C48. Needed for average and standard deviation calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counters M1011C47 and M1011C48 after a successful location calculation.

kpi_info.title: SUM_EMISHO_LATENCY (M1011C50)
kpi_info.use: The sum of EMISHO latency. Measured from emergency location request arrival to point where ISHO is performed successfully. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C51, gives the average EMISHO latency. UPDATED:When the ISHO has been successfully performed, i.e. RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND, this counter is updated by the total duration of CI+RTT positioning and ISHO.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_EMISHO_LATENCY (M1011C51)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1011C50. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counter M1011C50 after a successful EMISHO.

kpi_info.title: EMISHO_LATENCY_LESS_THAN_2_S (M1011C52)
kpi_info.use: Number of EMISHOs where the time spent for EMISHO was less than 2 seconds. Measured from emergency location request arrival to point where ISHO has been successfully performed. UPDATED:When the ISHO has been successfully performed, i.e. RRCPRB receives iuv_iu_release_command_s message, and the total duration of CI+RTT positioning and ISHO was less than 2 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMISHO_LATENCY_BETW_2_TO_5_S (M1011C53)
kpi_info.use: Number of EMISHOs where the time spent for EMISHO was between 2 and 5 seconds. Measured from emergency location request arrival to point where ISHO has been successfully performed. UPDATED:When the ISHO has been successfully performed, i.e. RRCPRB receives iuv_iu_release_command_s message, and the total duration of CI+RTT positioning and ISHO was between 2 and 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMISHO_LATENCY_OVER_5_SEC (M1011C54)
kpi_info.use: Number of EMISHOs where the time spent for EMISHO was over 5 seconds. Measured from emergency location request arrival to point where ISHO has been successfully performed. UPDATED:When the ISHO has been successfully performed, i.e. RRCPRB receives iuv_iu_release_command_s message, and the total duration of CI+RTT positioning and ISHO was over 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: SUM_EMG_CIRTT_LATENCY (M1011C55)
kpi_info.use: The sum of CI+RTT method latency for emergency location requests. Measured from the point when emergency location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C56, gives the average CI+RTT method latency for emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method, this counter is updated by the duration of the CI+RTT method.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_EMG_CIRTT_METHOD (M1011C56)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1011C55. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counter M1011C55 after a successful location calculation.

kpi_info.title: EMG_CIRTT_LAT_LESS_THAN_2_S (M1011C57)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage for emergency requests where the latency was less than 2 seconds. Measured from the point when emergency location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was less than 2 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMG_CIRTT_LAT_BETW_2_TO_5_S (M1011C58)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage for emergency requests where the latency was between 2 and 5 seconds. Measured from the point when emergency location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was between 2 and 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMG_CIRTT_LAT_OVER_5_S (M1011C59)
kpi_info.use: Number of CI+RTT position method usage for emergency requests where the latency was over 5 seconds. Measured from the point when emergency location request has been received by RNC to point when CI+RTT position has been calculated in SMLC. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by CI+RTT method and the duration was over 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: SUM_EMG_GPS_LATENCY (M1011C60)
kpi_info.use: The sum of GPS method latency. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position for emergency location request has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C61, gives the average GPS latency for emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by UE based A-GPS, NW based A-GPS or standalone method, this counter is updated by the duration of the GPS method.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_EMG_GPS_METHOD (M1011C61)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counter M1011C60. Needed for average calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counter M1011C60.

kpi_info.title: EMG_GPS_LAT_LESS_THAN_5_S (M1011C62)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was less than 5 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position for emergency location request has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by UE based A-GPS, NW based A-GPS or standalone method and the duration was less than 5 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMG_GPS_LAT_BETW_5_TO_15_S (M1011C63)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was between 5 and 15 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position for emergency location request has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by UE based A-GPS, NW based A-GPS or standalone method and the duration was between 5 and 15 seconds.

kpi_info.title: EMG_GPS_LAT_OVER_15_SEC (M1011C64)
kpi_info.use: Number of GPS position method usage where the latency was over 15 seconds. Measured from the point when CI+RTT position for emergency location request has been calculated in SMLC to point where GPS position is available. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated by UE based A-GPS, NW based A-GPS or standalone method and the duration was over 15 seconds.

kpi_info.title: SUM_EMG_LCS_TOTAL_LATENCY (M1011C65)
kpi_info.use: The sum of total LCS latency, including RTT and RxTx measurements, CI+RTT method calculation and possible A-GPS positioning. Measured from the point when emergency location request has been received by SMLC to point when location response has been sent to CN from SMLC. This counter, divided by the denominator M1011C67, gives the average LCS latency for emergency requests. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated and the response has been sent to CN, this counter is updated by the duration of the location procedure.

kpi_info.title: SUM_SQR_EMG_LCS_TOT_LATENCY (M1011C66)
kpi_info.use: The sum of squared emergency LCS latency. Needed for standard deviation calculation. UPDATED:When the location of UE (emergency call) has been successfully calculated and the response has been sent to CN, this counter is updated by the squared duration of the location procedure.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_EMG_LCS_TOTAL_LATENCY (M1011C67)
kpi_info.use: The denominator for the counters M1011C65 and M1011C66. Needed for average and standard deviation calculation. UPDATED:When the duration value is updated to counters M1011C65 and M1011C66.

kpi_info.title: REJECT_DIR_LOC_REQ_DUE_CAPA (M1011C68)
kpi_info.use: The number of rejected direct location requests due to lack of LCS capacity. UPDATED:When the RNC rejects direct location request and the reason is lack of LCS capacity. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: REJECT_PER_LOC_REQ_DUE_CAPA (M1011C69)
kpi_info.use: The number of rejected periodical location requests due to lack of LCS capacity. UPDATED:When the RNC rejects periodical location request and the reason is lack of LCS capacity. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: LOC_REP_WITH_CELL_GAI (M1011C70)
kpi_info.use: Total number of sent location response with the successful Cell GAI coordinates as location estimate when UE is in anchoring. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RANAP: Location Report including Cell GAI. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: LOC_REP_WITHOUT_CELL_GAI (M1011C71)
kpi_info.use: Total number of sent location response without Cell GAI coordinates when UE is in anchoring. UPDATED:When the RNC sends RANAP: Location Report without Cell GAI in anchoring case. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: LCS_REQUESTS_FOR_TRACE (M1011C72)
kpi_info.use: The number of Subscriber Trace triggered location requests received by SMLC. These requests are generated internally in the RNC when feature "RAN1311 Position Information in Subscriber Trace Report" is enabled. Trace related location requests do not update counter M1011C0 LCS REQUESTS. UPDATED:When the SLMC entity receives Subscriber Trace related location request.

kpi_info.title: FAIL_LCS_REQUESTS_FOR_TRACE (M1011C73)
kpi_info.use: The number of Subscriber Trace triggered location requests that could not be served by SMLC. Trace related location requests do not update counter M1011C2 FAILED LCS REQUESTS . UPDATED:When the SLMC is not able to return any position for a location request triggered by Subscriber Trace.
